The paper discusses the use of similarity measures in Author Cocitation Analysis, which is a technique commonly used in Information Retrieval (IR) and Digital Libraries (DL) research. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions clustering and non-parametric statistics, which are topics covered in cs.SI and cs.LG. Finally, the paper discusses the use of correlation coefficients, which is a topic covered in cs.CC.
